data.title: Furniture and Mattress Store Near Me
data.meta_description: Shop for furniture, mattresses, and home décor at your Arlington, TX Ashley Store. Visit our showroom today to furnish your home affordably.
data.text:
Worst experience ever. I do NOT recommend going to this Ashley store. I order a king bed set from them which I made extremely easy by going in there and already knowing exactly what I wanted. The guy that helped me didn’t have to do much. I told him I was moving and needed the bed set. I paid for delivery and setup. He said make sure I respond quickly with delivery which I did. It was going to be delivered on a Friday. Since I picked assembly I knew it would take a moment. So I took off work for that day. The day before I get a call that the king bed is “lost”. She had no update when it would be in and was extremely unhelpful. I then did the Ashley chat online and waited for them to tell me I have no order placed with their company. I left work and went to the store I purchased at. Between this I messaged the guy who I purchased with which I got zero responses. I then get to the store and he is laughing in a corner and we lock eyes and as I go to the counter he sends me a text sorry I’m on lunch. He clearly was not. I then speak to the manager Megan and tell her the situation. She cuts me off multiple times. Tells me over an over to give her until the end of the day. So I said is that 5 o’clock? You close at 9? She said yes around 5 I will reach out. At 7pm I call her since I’ve heard nothing. which she doesn’t answer and instead sends me a text message saying it shows the 7th now. Couldn’t even call me though. The 7th passes and they have no update. I have cancelled my king bed set and will not ever be going back to this store. Their communication all around is horrible!!! Why you would think texting as a manager is acceptable I have no clue. Save your time & money and go somewhere else!

Totally disappointed. Bought a bedroom set from here and was so excited, thinking I had made the best choice and was getting the best quality. Wow, was I wrong. Regretting my decision to purchase from here instead of HomeZone or Rooms to Go. Lesson learned. My sales rep, Eric, was super slow and less than helpful but I fell in love with the pieces and had to have it. He personally vouched for an independent moving company that was unprofessional and RUDE to pick up and deliver the piece. They came with no prior notice and were argumentative when I asked for a receipt. A request which I had made prior to delivery, even threating to "just return my items to the store". Then I get the dresser and it's rocking. They tell me it can't be serviced since I bought the showroom piece. Seems like if you're going to sell some one a piece "as-is" you should be honest about any flaws in the product before they take that deal. Definitely feel like Ashley's sold me a lemon. The delivery service was subpar, my original delivery date was 11/29, then I randomly getting a call, telling me to select a date and the soonest available is 12/5. Confused, I attempted to use the customer service chat option only to be greeted by a rep and then completely ignored when I expressed my concerns. The next day I get a new call from Ashley's to schedule the delivery, this time for 12/1. Hopefully, it actually happens this time. Lesson definitely learned.

Extremely Disappointed with Ashley Homestore's Unreceived Furniture I cannot express how profoundly disappointed I am with my recent experience with Ashley Homestore's Arlington Store. After fully paying for my furniture order, I have yet to receive two of the items I purchased. This has been an absolute inconvenience, and I feel compelled to share my unfortunate experience with others. I placed my order for a pair of motorized adjustable height desk set from this location with great excitement. The selection and prices seemed excellent, and I have had a good experience about the brand's quality after purchasing a master bedroom set few years back. After completing my purchase and eagerly anticipating the arrival of my new furniture, I was shocked to find the desks delivered were the incorrect color. I reached out to the store and their customer service department multiple times, but the responses were generic and contradictory but as of date there is no clear ETA on the arrival except a six week window with no guarantees. This is simply unacceptable for a business that relies on its customers' trust and satisfaction. What is most frustrating is the fact that I paid for these items in full, and I have received absolutely nothing in return except a small credit for the delivery. It's as if my hard-earned money has simply vanished into thin air. This has caused some stress on my health as I am constantly sitting and the inconvenience that I could have avoided by choosing a more reliable furniture retailer. I sincerely hope that others will read this review and think twice before ordering from Ashley Homestore Arlington. My experience has been nothing short of a major inconvenience, and I strongly advise against doing business with them until they can demonstrate a significant improvement in their customer service and fulfillment processes. In conclusion, I cannot emphasize enough how disheartened I am by Ashley Homestore's complete lack of commitment to customer satisfaction. If you value your time, money, and sanity, I would strongly recommend looking elsewhere for your furniture needs.

I had originally posted a good review, because in store it seemed decent, Laika(sp) was wonderful and friendly and didn’t pressure us like other stores, however that is the extent of the good experience…it went downhill fast! First we were told about 2-3 weeks to be able to pick up our mattress from warehouse, I thought ok not bad it’s a California king (bed in a box deal) so maybe not as readily available. So then I texted the customer support line to see if could get updates about our order and was told 2-16 weeks like what?!?!? It took about 10 weeks with 2 date push backs before we FINNALLY were able to get it! Ok fine irritated about that but finally got it to replace our old breaking down one, so we leave it out longer than box’s suggestion of 48 hours, we almost hit 72 hours maybe 4 hrs shy of it. When we put it up it was soooo flimsy on one side it kept almost dumping my husband out of the bed, so we contacted the support again. Oh you have to wait a month to make a warranty claim on this, cause it may keep inflating (how with two adults on it idk but hey ok) Fine so we wait said 30 days on an uncomfortable mattress that also had feelings of misaligned springs or easily falling out of bed due to no support, do the support line, have to schedule inspection, so another 2 weeks of uncomfortable bed, with their supposed comfort guarantee. The inspector said bed has half inch dip in middle and it’s normal wear and tear! You kidding me?!? Only 1.5 months and it’s already sinking in?!?! So that mean it’ll be done in less than a yr 🙄, and they don’t care if you aren’t happy with the item they just say nothing they can do, so we spent our hard earned money to be screwed over by false promises of satisfaction! Won’t be getting anything else from this company again!

I came in with dilemmas and I have been to so many different places trying to figure out what I could get to fit in my apartment that has very tight spaces and Vincent came up to me as soon as I walked in the door and made sure I was taken care of the whole way through. I put him through the ringer and he never dropped his smile. I had to leave without purchase and come back with pictures and measurements 2 Days later, and the first place I seen when I walked in the door was Vincent. A set of customers walked in before me and he greeted them and told me to give him a sec and in a few he was back at it again with me making sure I was good. He literally took me through every avenue he could think of until I reached the final decision one that is completely different from my vision but Grand all the same and well protected I couldn't be more grateful for anything and all others that came and advised. Needless to say I appreciate the experience this store had to offer.. the grace alone is enough... Most people would not take out the time to stick with a customer like me... Especially not for 2 days 🤗

Upon entering the store I said HELLO ASHLEY then I looked around for about 10min until a saleman name Jose Villafane greeting me with so much respect and he said welcome to Ashley how can I help you and I pulled out my phone and said I would like this and he said let me go check and I will be right back. He came back and said I apologize we do not have that in the store I said DARN! But I knew I wasn't leaving Ashley until I brought something. I said ok, I need a high queen-sized bed frame and he said I will show you 12inch/24inch. I said no only show me 24inch, he said ok. The very last one he showed me I said I'll take it and then I said I need a mattress, he said follow me. He said now which one would you like I said this one and he went on explaining to me about the mattress. We go checkout and I said I need a twin bed frame but I ran out of money. I said I will return shortly and I came back with my son and my son said Mom why you buying this little bed I said so family will not stay we all laugh. Get to the checkout I said Jose give me a full size bed frame instead and I will go to Costco for a mattress and he said wait Ms.Thompkins let me do something I said ok. He turn around and said how do like this mattress for $289.00 my son said I'll take it and mother looked at son and son said Mom you can't beat that Mom said you are absolutely right. I said Jose you didn't want me to go to Costco keep it all right here for Ashley right so we all started laughing. Smooth. Mother/Son thank everyone and left.

I ordered a coffee table and two end tables in Nov 2021. We chose to pick up the tables from the warehouse, instead of delivery. Pick up of the tables was rescheduled 3 times and I was finally able to pick up the last of my order today, August 5, 2022. Along the way there was zero communication on the part of Ashley’s. It was up to me to call customer service and see what the status of my order was. (Ona side note, I had also ordered furniture from two other stores in Nov 2021 and those two store keep me apprised of my order status all on their own.) However, customer service did call yesterday to say my tables had finally arrived and were ready for pick up. Great, I told them I would be there today to pick up. She said to show up anytime between 9-6. When I got there this afternoon and told the woman behind the desk that I was there to pick up she said it would be a 30-60 minute wait. At no point did the woman from customer service yesterday tell me to expect a wait so long. She made it sound like they would have everything pulled and waiting for pick up. This is not the case. Had I know I would be waiting 45 minutes, I would have arranged my day differently. The waiting room was complete chaos when I arrived, as there were three irate customers already there. There was yelling and screaming coming from both the customers and Ashley’s employees. The employees behind the counter were extremely rude (two woman and one man). One of the customers even ended up calling the police. Thankfully my furniture was pulled before the police arrived. I do not know what the outcome was, but I do completely understand the three other customers feeling of frustration. The complete lack of customer service that I experienced personally as a customer and then witnessed in the waiting room was astounding. I will definitely not be a repeat customer or be recommending Ashley’s to anyone I know.

0/5 would recommend 1. We received a call from Ashley’s saying the item we had picked ($699.99, not including tax or delivery fee) was discounted and that we could stop by to reselect or cancel. We were already not pleased with the service so we decided to cancel. We went to the store and we only got a refund for $480. Yup, that’s right they took a fee for them discounting the item. 2. When we first went in to the store to pick our items the sales man did not tell us he was including the protection ($300) on the two items we were purchasing. I ask for the total before he took our Ashley’s credit card and he specifically told us it was 1500 when in reality is was 1800 because he included the the insurance WITHOUT ASKING. My husband and I walked outside with our folder and finally got to see the itemized bill. We were upset at seeing the additional charges. I immediately walked back inside and he didn’t even know want to say when confronted. He made the changes on the itemized bill and we signed. I thankfully asked for a copy. Afterwards, there was email communication in which we were assured that the unwanted insurance was getting removed. After waiting additional time for our first delivery, the insurance was STILL listed on it delivery statement. I eventually had to call the Ashley’s credit card and I am currently working with them to get the charge disputed. 3. Overall, Ashley has taken about $600 from us and we have literally nothing to show for it (we are praying that our dispute gets approved and we can at least a get $300 back). That’s money that we worked hard to save for the nursery of our first baby. I’m mad at myself because pregnancy brain is real and unfortunately I am not as alert as usual when it comes to all this. I went to to Ashley’s because I THOUGHT they were a trusting place but they aren’t! They take advantage of people. We will NEVER go back to Ashley’s and we will make sure none of our family and friends do either. On the other hand, we 10/10 would recommend you visit the Nebraska furniture store instead. We had an amazing experience and they have free delivery! The furniture for our nursery will be delivered THIS week. No need to wait weeks for your furniture!

Dining set: Johnelle collection round table with 6 chairs. The deliverers were rushing out and did not really allow much time for a thorough look over. We had to run outside to catch them. I also thought that while they were careful enough bringing things inside, why is it that they do not level the furniture when they set it up considering the high cost for white glove delivery service fee of $189.99 plus tax. The leveling should be part of the set up process, but I was told to level the chairs myself. I refused 3 of 6 chairs but 2 more chairs were defective. One of them won’t level at all and the other has a stripped bolt where the legs meet the base of the chair cushion. The table base leg was scratched. I found all of this within 3-5 more minutes. Had they done the leveling and allowed me time to inspect closer, I could have refused all those things and saved myself the trouble of trying to get them replaced and still not have a complete dining set. I called the number to report the other items and was told they could not help because my delivery is still on the manifest for today and my order number is locked for up to 48 hours but Ashley only gives 72 hours after delivery to report issues. They tell me they have recorded what I said the issues were. No definite resolution has been made or can be made until my order is unlocked.

I just looked at my wrist, I have time today….. Let me first start by stating that Jeremie Magee is an excellent home furnishing AND customer care specialist! I grateful for my experience with him. I purchased 2 comforter sets from the store (not floor samples). Initially I did not check the bags to be certain all parts were included. They are supposed to be brand new. I ordered a bed for these comforters and when the bed came, I opened one of the comforters. At that moment, I discovered that all of the parts were not included. I then opened the other to discover the same. I was irritated to say the least. I went back to Ashley and Jeremie was as helpful as he possibly could be. He took me to BRITTANY who despite stating she is a customer care specialist was everything BUT that. The first words out of her mouth were “We have a 72 hour policy for exchanges and returns so there is nothing we can do.” I explained to her that the sets were not complete and asked if she could go check the back for the additional parts. She told me “no.” She proceeded to tell me about the contract I signed and that I should have read it, blah, blah, blah. It is true, I should have read it. That does not negate the fact that Ashley is a reputable store and I should be able to have full confidence in the products I purchase. If this were an expensive product, perhaps I would have been more apprehensive. My disappointment comes because there was absolutely no care or concern for me as a customer/consumer. One only has to review their records to see that I have spent THOUSANDS of dollars at Ashley, and to be flippantly dismissed as a customer with genuine concerns and not offered ANY assistance to make it right is unacceptable. At the very least, EXCHANGE the products for complete comforter sets or refund me for a defective product and take these from me. I will continue to share this particular experience with as many people as possible. Brittany needs a lesson in compassion and customer service. I believe in policies and procedures but I believe customer relationships are even more important.

It’s ten months now- still no furniture and no contact…. nobody willing to help or reach out and assist us to know what’s going on…manager will not call, either. Will be reaching out to BBB and bank in reference to charges from 1/01/22 an d purchase never received; no contact from store. They can’t charge for items, never deliver and not contact you or refund the money. So six months later, still missing three of the five pieces of furniture purchased January 01 that we were told were in stock and would receive the next week. We only received 2 of 5 pieces. Today, June 17, still have not received a call back from the manager. I have requested four separate times for a call back and an update and have not received a single call. Girl on phone today asked if WE have COME OUT TO THE STORE to check on the order…wow Will are filing a complaint with the Better Business Bureau. When did it become okay to take someone’s money and never respond with an answer about what we paid for, and avoid all contact and updates? We spent so much time shopping for and waiting on this, and now it is a complete eye sore. Two of five pieces…. We went somewhere else to furnish the other rooms and it was done in a professional and timely manor. Originally said Good quality furniture. Problem is sales people was not honest about the items being in stock- The gentleman who helps load your purchase if you pick up anything at the store, was a really nice and very helpful gentleman.He went above and beyond. As for the rest- was lied to for them to get the purchase. We were told everything was in stock and would deliver next week. It didn’t happen. When I called the store I was told they were on back order.. I was told by sales person that was out of their control, yet at time of purchase she was the one who said it’s all in stock- This type of service is not acceptable. I want people to be honest and up front. Not lied to in order to get the sale.

Before my November 26th. 2021 (Black Friday) purchase with Ashley Furniture, I had always purchased my furniture from Rooms to Go for the last 16 years. Funny enough I had just left Rooms to Go empty handed minutes before entering the Ashley furniture store in Arlington Tx. off of Cooper & I20. . . At this point I was only browsing, passing time and no longer taking my search for furniture serious because my loyalty had always been with Rooms to Go. I was greeted in the Ashley Furniture store around 10:17am by a young sales man name (Michael Robles/ Mike). I proceeded to walk around until I started to have a small anxiety attack because I was overly stimulated and by my surprise the young man (Mike) asked me if there was anything he could do; I asked him for space so I could have a moment to breath and I informed him I would need to look at the furniture in small increments so I could make the best decision. I was so surprised the young man was so patient with me. It really blessed my heart because I'm used to people judging me and trying to rush me like car salesmen. Mike spent 5½ hours with me as I had to take brakes in-between my search. I didn't feel judged or rushed, he was so professional and kind. After my 5½ hour transaction, I left the store and called my friend and in the process of trying to tell her about my experience I almost started to cried because of the patient's he had with me (I'm not crier) but I was just moved by his kindness. I'm in my late 30's, and I have made SEVERAL BIG TICKET PURCHASES, cars, homes etc. and in all my years I have NEVER experienced better customer service. I'm used to being treated differently because I have a disability that people can't see on the surface but I didn't feel judged with Mike, He didn't make me feel like a dollar and he didn't care if I even purchased anything from the store or not. He CHOOSE to devote 5½ hours of his time despite the fact that he could have worked with several other customers and made tons of commission on Black Friday out of all day's of the year. Mike wasn't in it for the money. I have been 100% converted over to Ashley furniture because of this young man. If you're ever in the Arlington Tx. area ask for Michael Robles/ Mike for short , he's a great guy and the Manager of the store was such a sweet lady. Note: Being a genuinely good person cannot be taught, it has to already be in you. This store was full of diversity and some of the most kindest people you will ever meet. I compared this Ashley Furniture to my friend as "If Chick-fil-A was a furniture store".

During the holidays, Christmas time, I was in a need to replace my old leather couch, love seat and lazy boy, which I bought from Ashley 15 years ago. It is a heavy set of furniture that I would not be able to move just me and my wife. I stopped by the Ashley store in Arlington, the same store I originally bought my old furniture from 15 years ago. Which throughout years I spent thousands of dollars in. There was a nice piece of L shape couch that my wife loved, and thought it will fit nicely in our living area. We were hesitant at first, but after a couple of visits we decided to go with it, in the condition that they will help us move our old set to the garage. We met this nice salesman at the store his name was Cedric. He promised that delivery crew will help move old furniture to garage. I cleared my garage the night before. Delivery call early in the morning around 7 am the next day, while I was starting my work day from home. As they arrived around 9 am. I asked them to help move my old furniture to garage, they refused. I told them I was promised at store that they are going to help. They didn't budge. I even offered them some tip they didn't care. I am working from, very eager to go back to my work, and I thought I was a customer for Ashley who spent a good amount of money and this is how I get treated. I would rather spend my money somewhere else instead of dealing with their lying salesman and uncooperative delivery crew. Stay away if you can there are better stores who respect their customers.

To start I went in on Memorial Day to purchase some furniture. I had a warranty credit. The 1st lady that helped me had no interest in helping me. Due to an issue with the computer system I had to go home and get my paperwork and return. The lone bright spot in this whole purchase was Oliver who helped me when I returned. He was very helpful and professional. (He probably needs to find another company to work for) I pay the balance minus the credit and leave. Two weeks ago I started calling. I’ve called almost everyday and someone answered the phone once. That 1 time I was told that someone would call me back. That never happened. I continued to call and left voice messages the last 3 days. I used the chat on the website and the rep tells me that they can’t help me with purchases made in the store and suggested that I go in the store. So today I stop by. Come to find out my order has not been placed. They want to place the order today and tell me it will be another 4-6 weeks before I will receive the furniture that I paid for on Memorial Day. All the store can offer is an I’m sorry. While I’m in the store talking with the manager there’s another woman in the store that has been waiting on some furniture that she’s purchased a while back as well. This seems to be standard operating procedure with them. The only reason they get 1 star is because they don’t offer 0.

Edit: I have dropped my rating from 2 to 1 star. Despite their notice below Ashley's furniture did nothing to help. They simply indicated that they could nothing about the issues I was experiencing via email and gave me the run around on subsequent calls. I have since received my mattress, but the tables have been delayed for another 4-6 weeks as of today, July 8. Be aware if you purchase from this store and are in a rush. You may end up waiting a lot longer than they say in store. I was initially impressed by the sales team. The sales representative who helped me took time to walk me through the entire store, taking into consideration my budget and preferences. I left the store after purchasing a bed frame, an adjustable base and mattress, a set of tables (including a coffee table and two end tables), and a reclining sofa. The sales representative informed me that I would receive most of my furniture at the same time, except for the bed frame, which would arrive separately. This was not an issue, since I would only need the mattress for the time being. The problems started arising when it came to delivery. When I received the call to schedule my first delivery, I was informed that I would receive everything except for the mattress and adjustable base. The mattress and base would not be ready for delivery until at least June 10. This was contrary to what I was expecting. This was annoying but I decided to leave it be, as I was still in the process of moving. I scheduled the first delivery for June 5. On the day of June 5, my delivery arrived. However, I was informed that the set of tables I ordered was not included in that shipment (despite being on the delivery receipt). I called as soon as the delivery personnel left and was informed that my tables had been delayed until the 26th. Again, I was unhappy however since they were just tables I left it alone. However, today, June 8, I received another call confirming my next delivery, which I was expecting to include both the mattress and adjustable base. However, I was informed that only the adjustable base was ready and the mattress was not expected to arrive in their warehouse until the 18th. This is unsatisfactory. I now have to wait until the 19th before my mattress and bedframe are delivered (assuming there are no more delays). I am highly disappointed by the poor communication. It was my understanding that most of my items were in stock and would be shipped all at once. It's inconvenient for me to have to work around multiple deliveries because of arbitrary delays. Had I known of the potential for such delays I would have likely made some of my purchases elsewhere.

My wife put a bedroom set in layaway here and continued to pay monthly for a couple of years and right when she was ready to pay it off they told her the bedroom set was discontinued. What was very aggravating is they continued to collect the layaway money even after they discontinued the bedroom set without telling my wife. On top of all this in January my wife asked for a full refund of $4812.24 dollars and it is now May and my wife still haven’t received all her money back. We escalated the refund to the better business bureau and they say they approved the refund on February 7 but mailed her return to a wrong address. Even though the paperwork has our correct address. My wife is still waiting for her full refund 5 months later. We have been in person several times to get her refund, contacted corporate several times still no refund they keep giving excuses and take their time to give her money back. It is now May and they have not refunded the full amount and still owe her over $3061.24 They gave her a partial refund in April. We never received any product were just trying to get all our layaway money back but so far we have not got all our money back and been trying since January. They sate contact us below and were sorry for the way this has been handled thus far. We have given all the information they asked for below more than once and they apologize making it look like they need the info again. It would be nice if they would refund our money. This has been one of the most frustrating experiences we have been through with any business. As of May 7, 2021 My wife still has not received a full refund. They keep telling us it’s in the mail. 5 months to wait for a full refund ! We just found out on May 13 that they mailed the refund to the WRONG ADDRESS AGAIN! This company can’t do anything correctly, we’re beginning to think they are doing this intentionally! We have honest neighbors they brought the refund that Ashley’s sent to their address. This was the second time Ashley’s sent separate checks to another address that wasn’t ours. They admitted it to the BBB and the turn around and make the same error again! Me and my wife will never do business with Ashley’s again EVER!!!!!!!!!!!!!!’

Made an order of 6k+ of furniture in September during their Labor Day sale and they said items were in back order and will arrive late October, which was fine. They kept pushing back the date and then finally set a date in early December to deliver SOME furniture and the day of delivery they cancel without notice! We had to call and ask where our furniture was as they said the distribution center had canceled our partial delivery. They rescheduled the delivery for Dec 24th and when it came close to deliver date they called and reschedule, this happened sooo many times. Keep in mind it was only partial delivery this whole time and the rest of our furniture wasn’t getting here till May! We ended up canceling the furniture because it seemed like we were never going to receive our furniture!! The salesperson that helped us named Ronald Lewis, sold us a mattress that was back ordered for TEN YEARS! We had no idea and wouldn’t have even known if we hadn’t went back a couple days later after placing the order to add a couple of more items that another salesperson told us the mattress was backordered. As well when we went back the second time we added this rug that was $500+ and the salesperson Valerie Benitez said we were going to get the one of the floor. I asked if they were going to clean it or if we could get a discount as it has been stepped on by other people and she said no, we were getting it as is. You’d expect for that price of a rug to receive a new one, not something that has been used! Ashley’s is THE WORST place to buy furniture from! I would never recommend someone to buy from them! I NEVER do reviews but Ashley’s has made my blood boil! And i wish I could rate them zero stars!! I hope someone reads this review so they don’t buy anything from them and can save themselves from getting headaches! Cancelled our order Jan 11th with Ashelys and the same day we went Havertys and we got our furniture the next day!

I purchased a leather sofa from this store on December 23, 2020. It was scheduled for pick it up on Thursday, December 31, but it was raining. I called the sales representative and asked if I could pick it up the next day instead and he said that would be o.k. I asked if they were going to be open since it was a holiday and he stated that they should be because their store was open. I called the call center and they told me that that my order was available for pick up. I told them that I was on the way. When my husband arrived, the distribution center was closed. No one bothered to tell me that we could not pick up the sofa when I called. He went back the next day to pick it up. Once we got it home and opened it, I noticed two small cuts on the back, bottom of the sofa. This is a sight no one wants to see on a brand new purchase. Once again, I called the sales representative and even sent him pictures of the damages. He talked to his manager and informed me that I would have to return sofa within twenty four hours and get a replacement. As much trouble as we had getting it, there was no way we were going to return it. This would not only involve another trip to the store, but also enlisting yet another person to help my husband with removal, as the couch is quite heavy. I asked him if they just give me a discount and I never heard back from anyone.

THIS STORE IS THE WORST!!! I should have took the sign of going in on a Friday night not being greeted and having to seek out help as a sign. I came in to replace mattresses lost in a fire and specifically requested what I purchased before (a year ago) from Ashley's. The sales agent LOVELY looked up my info, informed me one set was discontinued and not carried at Ashley's, then showed me something else while during the entire interaction she failed to answer my questions directly multiple times about price. UNACCEPTABLE. Decisions were made and I landed on a purchase only to find out later that the "discontinued" item I initially asked for WAS in fact AVAILABLE and now LOVELY had actually UPSOLD me on another mattress set. Trying to address the matter via phone was impossible. You CANNOT call the store directly despite the phone number provided on correspondence and business cards and calling general customer service to only promise they will escalate the matter to a higher up in the local store to address within 48 hours is a TOTAL JOKE. I had to go back up to the store, request an adjustment to my order resulting in a credit back to my card that was "supposed" to take 7-10 business days. DID NOT HAPPEN. I had to make another trip up to the store as making phone calls resulted in nothing and I did not have time to waste; it wasn't until then someone told me the credit was never processed. Took nearly 2 months to get the mattresses with delivery dates changing 4 different times AND zero communication being initiated by Ashley's of the changes. EACH time I had to contact Ashley's to figure out what the hell was going on?! The other set of mattresses I needed I opted to go to Mattress Firm around the corner who had a great deal offered, better quality, and could deliver in just a couple of days for no additional charge. GO TO MATTRESS FIRM INSTEAD!!! I will never shop at THIS store or Ashley's period. I work in customer service for a financial services firm and majority of my interactions with associates who work for Ashley's could use some training as it pertains to EQ skills and embodying a high EQ. Please do not go to sales agent Lovely where the interaction will be anything BUT lovely, more less disastrous, horrific, atrocious. THE ONLY SALES AGENT THAT IS TOP NOTCH AT THIS LOCATION IS MR. ANTONIO BASS.

My husband, Keith, and I have had a series of unfortunate interactions and disappointments with getting furniture we ordered back in May on Memorial weekend. We waited 3 months to get our delivery of furniture. We ordered 3 Darcy sofas in Mocha, one being a sleeper sofa for the center of our living room, and one ottoman. Upon delivery, the sleeper was a totally different color. We were told it was a simple encoding error with the numbers being transposed by the salesperson. The delivery team came back later the same day and picked up the odd colored sleeper. We were upset at having missing furniture, but we were promised an expedited delivery of the correct product. The issue then was not only more time without the furniture we purchased, but now we are being told that we’d need to wait until October 5th for the sleeper to arrive. So from May 23rd to August 22nd to October 5th – being made promises to make things right!! When we went to the store in August, Johnny, Store Manager, assured us that we would get our sleeper to complete our set, and if Ashley couldn’t fulfill the order, then we could get another set. We contacted Ashley on Wednesday, October 7th to inquire about our missing sleeper, only to be told that it was discontinued!!! There would be No sleeper coming! Since May!? Since August!? It’s October!!! We went to the Ashley store in Arlington on Thursday, the 8th, around 3:00 PM, and there was a sign on front door, saying the store was closed for cleaning. We returned on Friday afternoon, the 9th, and spoke with Johnny, Store Manager, and Lovely, our salesperson. With no hopes of our sleeper, we decide we can swap it for a large sectional to fill the space where the three sofas were to go. We were told that none of the larger sectionals had sleeper, nor were there any sleepers we liked available until the first of the year 2021!!!! OMG!!!! I cannot believe we had faith in this situation being resolved timely or professionally. We told Johnny he needed to honor his word, and he got upset and loud. We apparently were the third of three customers all in awaiting furniture, and he had lost his patience. He was so rude to the point where his Assistant Manager (not sure of name. Bald guy with blue eyes) and Lovely asked him to go to the back, and they would handle it. We no longer want an incomplete set, and we have waited far too long at this point for a solid and fair resolution. We want to get our Mocha Darcy sleeper ASAP, or return the two sofas and ottoman to you. It looks totally crazy to have a big space just empty in the middle of our living room. I am sad because we have been furnishing our homes with Ashley since 2003. The Darcy was our previous set, and we simply wanted new items. Can you please make this right? We cannot wait until January for furnish we ordered in May 2020. Please contact Keith or me. Thank you!!

I ordered a sectional from Ashley's in July. It was scheduled to be delivered the second week of September. September came and Ashleys called me to set up a delivery time and confirmation. I was excited to finally be receiving the sectional but it was never delivered that day. No one from ashleys called or told me anything regarding what happened. I ended up calling them to find out that my sectional was delayed until 4 to 7 weeks. I was very disappointed that no one notified me and that I hadn't received my furniture. However I do understand that due to Covid things are different so I was not to upset. I then phsically went to Ashley's a few weeks later to cancel my order because I felt as if I was not going to receive my furniture. When I made to the location, I spoke with an employee who pulled my information up and advised that my section would be ready by Oct 8th and that I would get a call 1 to 2 days prior to set up delivery and that the ottoman that comes with the sectional will arrive in November. I figured I'm not as worried about the ottoman as long as I receive the sectional since Oct 8 was about a week and a half away so I can wait. Well October 8th came and I did not receive a call. I then contacted Ashley's and was informed that those dates are just estimated times and that the sectional would be there soon. I was then told everything would arrive in November. At this point I'm very disappointed and frustrated and just want to cancel everything!

Shorter version: inconsistent and misleading answers to questions, delivery date pushed out twice as long as we agreed to, no way to contact the store directly when issues arose, 10% cancel fee even when requested because of their poor service and within a few days of ordering (before they even started building the furniture). They had no issue taking our money upfront even though they won't deliver the product for over 12 weeks. Still waiting for them to contact us even once after several calls and returning to the store to speak with them in person. Longer version: Visited store and found furniture we liked. Spoke with sales associate and store manager who told us final price and next available delivery date (5-6 weeks out from that day) which we agreed to. Manager tells us we can select exact delivery date with sales associate when we go back to office area and pay. We pay, then she tells us we can't choose delivery date right away, but someone will contact us within 72 hours to schedule it. We hear nothing for 5 days, so I called the "store" number (found on Google and listed on our receipt) but it's a call center and they tell us there's no way to call the store directly or reach the manager we met with. They can only tell us that our furniture will not be ready until 12 weeks later, and that we're unable to schedule delivery until after it has arrived at their local warehouse. So we're likely looking at 4 months after the date we paid for it by the time we actually receive it. I call back again (on the off chance that another call center staff member may be more helpful or able to connect us to the store) and are told an even later date this time. Both call center staff told me they'd put in a request to have the store call me back, and that I should hear something within 24 hours. Never heard anything back. I finally drove to the store (45 min away) so I could try to get a straight answer and see about canceling if they couldn't deliver sooner. Spoke with manager and he told me they actually needed two more weeks before they could determine more accurate delivery date, and made excuses for why he and the sales associate told us differently on the date of purchase. I mentioned canceling and he said it would be a 10% fee since the order had been placed (even though he'd already told me nothing had been started with our furniture). Not wanting to lose hundreds of dollars, we decided to wait and see what happens and hope things improve. If not, we can still cancel anytime prior to delivery for that same fee. At this point we're still waiting to see what happens. The only reason they get 2 stars is because the furniture does appear to be good quality and solid. We'll know for sure if it ever gets delivered.

My husband and l were in the market to buy new living room furniture during the pandemic and our 1st stop was Ashley Home Furniture in Arlington. We were greeted nicely by a gentleman named RJ whom we'd work with diligently going forward. He was considerably knowledgeable about what our interests were and if he wasn't certain about something, he'd patiently seek out the info. After finding something that both my husband and l agreed to, l found the same furniture at a competitive location with a cheaper cost. After leaving Ashley to check out the competitive store I still didn't feel right about getting the furniture at the cheapest place. I took the time to read about Ashley's insurance/warranty and how well they responded to any foreseeable issues customers have with the furniture. While also researching reviews on the competition and their returns, or issues and needless to say it wasn't as good. So l called RJ to see if they could do a price match and he said sure! So back to Ashley's we went to pick out a couch, recliner chair for my husband and an ottoman/ table for the couch and an in table. Now, its the beginning of August and our furniture will be here at the earliest in October or latest in November, but that's understandable because of the Pandemic we're in. But thankfully we didn't get rid of our old furniture just yet. The only reason I gave a 4 star is because of the wait time and because I am going to give a follow-up on the durability of the furniture in 6 months to a year after having it. The warranty is refundable (with the purchase of something else) if you don't have to use it during the time to have it, which is something I liked also. Overall I'm pleased with the experience that I had with Ashley's Home Furniture.

I'm feeling pretty jilted by this store at the moment. My husband and I purchased a sofa on 6/6/2020 for about $2k and were told we would receive a call the next week to set up delivery. Expecting to receive a couch, we sold ours so the room was ready.. We heard nothing the entire next week. I finally called the week after and the rep told me our had been a bit delayed and I would hear something then next week, also, get updates via text every 8 days. After 2 more weeks of not hearing anything, I called again. This time the rep told me there was actually a mistake on our order and someone had put in a 2021 delivery date, we should get a call for delivery the next week. ..... again 2 more weeks of not hearing anything and I call again. This rep tells us that shipping is delayed and that our sofa will be in by 7/24, but the ottoman is delayed, so they can set up a split delivery and get us our sofa as soon as it comes in and the ottoman later. I was perfectly ok with that.... as we've been sitting on the floor for over a month. Then, few days later, I get a text saying the expected arrival time for our furniture is 8/31. Hoping this was just regarding the ottoman, I call to make sure. The rep checks my order and says, oh yeah, your sofa is in so its about the ottoman. Then he puts me on hold while he sets up a delivery time. 15 mins later, he gets back on the phone and says he made a mistake, not only is our sofa not in, but now it won't be here until mid to late August. "But the ottoman may be in sooner if you'd like that delivered first." At this point, I am so angry that I ask to just cancel the order. I'm told that this has to be done through a manager, he would give them my info and they'd call me. This was 2 days ago...... still no call. Mind you, meanwhile we've both purchased and received a sofa for my husband's man cave from another store which had it to us within a week. I understand that COVID19 is causing delays, I get it. And had they been up front with us when we bought the furniture, this would have been different. But, instead, I was lied to.... several times. If they think people won't buy furniture if they say they're is going to be a delay, that's not true. We bought a bedroom set the same day from another furniture store that flat out told us they couldn't have it to us until the end of August, and we were fine with that. The difference? We didn't rush home and sell our bed! Because they were honest. I don't want this place to go out of business and I don't want anyone to lose their jobs. What I want is for them to stop jerking around people who have chosen to spend their hard earned money on one of their products. Meanwhile, I would not suggest anyone shop here.

Do not buy their expensive cheaply made furniture! So let's start at the beginning shall we... my wife and I decided it was time for a new loveseat, sofa and recliner. Looked at Ashley and saw a couple pieces we liked and could finance(through Ashley of course). Decided to make the deal, ordered our new furniture and awaited its delivery. We were sold the protection plans on each piece reluctantly but assured that it would cover literally anything that went wrong with each piece(since each requires it's own coverage and price). After we made the deal, signed the paperwork arranging the financing and all that jazz then we were informed the it would be a couple weeks before we would get the loveseat and recliner. But the sofa would take a month. Ok well would have been nice to know that BEFORE we purchased it! A couple of weeks goes by and sure enough got the call that the loveseat and recliner had showed up but still no word on the sofa? They had no idea at this point and were telling me that it would have to be made at the factory with a time frame still unknown. Wow these guys really dont have it together. So fast forward about a month or so and finally the sofa shows up and gets delivered, but we arent out of the woods yet. About a month later I go to sit down on the loveseat and I hear a loud crack and presto the board behind where your butt sits has broken in 2. So I call customer service, they setup a repair call and a few days later a tech comes out to fix it. I am observing him taking the bottom dust cover off and see that the whole thing is made out of 1/2" OSB board, heavy cardboard and basically inferior materials. We discussed how terribly it was constructed, how common they break as he went about doing his best to splice the broken support together with a metal bracket. He finishes it up and I notice he is using a crazy amount of staples on the lower inner armrest area. Ok I thought... so when he leaves I sit down and notice he ruined the armrest by bending the cardboard support under it creating a hard ridge that wasnt originally there. So I call Ashley again and in the end they decide to just replace the loveseat with another one which showed up a week or so after. Six months later the same butt board broke on the replacement loveseat and its sagging very noticeably in the middle. Called Ashley, because of COVID19 there is a longer than before wait for a tech to show but eventually one shows up. Same repair as before but he is unable to fix the sag because it's a design flaw and nothing short of modification can resolve it. He suggests calling Ashley, informing them of what he said and he leaves. I call Ashley and they say they will call me back about it. No one called. Eventually I call them and they informed me that the servicing is now handled by a different company and they will have to send their tech to look at it. Ugh. Rinse and repeat... so he showed up today, takes one look at it, repeats what the other guy said to a T and says the only way to fix it is by modifying it which voids the warranty. He said that from just sitting on it stretches out the webbing that holds the cushion support up and it's not serviceable at all, that it's a design flaw, that he will note it in his report and that I will have to get back with Ashley to see how they want to handle it. And he threw in that my sofa is sagging in the middle some, that's it's common for them to break in the middle since they have no center foot and I should tell Ashley asap so they can put a support in before it actually breaks. Nice. So it's been almost a year since ordering this stuff. A couple months short of a year and so far 2 loveseats have broken that were sort of repaired and one sagging sofa thats about 8 or so months old and here we are. Now I once again await another call from the customer service rep to see what awaits me now. If this is where I am in less than a year, I dont want to know what's in store for the next few years. How about take back this junk and refund my money Ashley!!!

We visited for the 4th of July sale and bought a new power recliner sofa and some bedroom furniture. Nelly was a huge help by explaining the features of each sofa we looked at and later the benefits of purchasing the platinum protection plan. Update: I am changing my rating after delivery and subsequent dealings with the protection plan. We paid for delivery and set up- the day my new sofa was delivered, the Ashley guys set it up. Literally the first time I used the mechanical recline feature, the sofa had been placed too close to the textured wall and the leather back panels got all scraped up. If I’m paying for delivery and set up, I’d expect that the movers at least know how far from the wall to place the item for the recline feature to work!! Making things worse: I was upset but it made me glad to have purchased the protection plan. I contacted platinum warranty, and they let me know that they do not cover damage that occurs on delivery or moving!!! This one time they are going to fix it “as a courtesy.” Along with that, When making the purchase in store, one of the biggest selling points for the protection plan made by Nelly, our sales associate, was that it would cover everything including any damage done by our dog (like nail scratches or tears) that might occur, and that something could happen literally every month and we could get it fixed under the plan. This pet damage was the main reason we ended up buying the plan!! I just got the protection plan info and it literally has a list of “exclusions” longer than the inclusions, and GUeSs WHaT? All pet damage besides wetting is excluded!! I feel like this was a huge gimmick. Very disappointed with the 100$ delivery and also the fact that we were basically lied to about the protection plan. Ask to see the laundry list of exclusions before you buy it because the little flyer that they give makes it look much better than it is.

I never comment on anything but I think it's important for everyone to know, NEVER order from Ashley! They're horrible! The furniture is beautiful. However, I ordered my furniture June 9th, it's July 26th and I still only have half of my order! They pushed back my estimated arrival date 4 times. They initially told me June 25, then July 7, then July 13 and then July 27! They didn't want to deliver any of my order until they could deliver it all at once! Meanwhile I'm in my brand new home with no couches or even a bed to sleep on and they wanted me to wait another 2 weeks to have everything delivered! They finally agreed to make 2 separate deliveries so I could at least have a bed to sleep on BUT they wanted to charge me for the second delivery! It was absolutely ridiculous and frustrating! The manager finally agreed to waive the fee but now I'm dealing with a nightstand that was broken upon delivery and them wanting to postone my couches being delivered another week just so they can deliver the nightstand with it! Now I'm looking at my couches and nightstand not being delivered until about August 8th unless I'm willing to pay for an extra delivery! That's an entire 2 MONTHS after placing my initial order!! This company has absolutely ruined the excitement of buying and furnishing my first home! I will never buy from them again and would tell anyone not to either!

This has been one of the worst buying experiences I’ve ever had. We were approved for a certain amount of financing and signed the financing agreement. The furniture is supposed to take about 4 weeks to arrive. Two weeks go by as we’re waiting for our furniture and we receive a call from our salesperson saying our financing didn’t get approved for that amount, and instead were only approved for half of the original amount. They said we would have to come back in and sign a whole new agreement. I told them I already signed a contract and got approved for a certain amount but they said they couldn’t control it because it was the finance company. They give us a small discount for our troubles. So I have to get my wife, daughter and 5 month old baby and go spend another hour up there signing new paperwork. The day our furniture arrives I call up there and they tell me that we have to come up there once again because they entered the wrong amount on the financing agreement and the financing company wouldn’t accept it. This is after I already signed a second contract and I’m again being told that it doesn’t matter if I signed a contract because they didn’t accept it. Why didn’t they call me to let me know about the issues right away? Instead I had to find out by calling up there the day our furniture arrives only to find out I would have to go out there again to spend another hour signing paperwork with my wife and 5 month old baby. I had to ask hem if they were going to do anything to make this right since we had to be greatly inconvenienced because of their mistakes. They gave me 3% off and said that’s all they could do. This will be the third time we have to go up there to sign a new contract. I just don’t understand why you have someone sign an agreement when it’s not even approved. There is no accountability here. Ashley’s Furniture does not care about their customers, only the sale. I like their furniture, but from a stand point of management and accountability it’s been a terrible experience and we will never shop here again. **Update** Ashley’s customer care team reached out to me and worked to resolve the issues along with some additional discounts for our troubles. We received our furniture and we’re very happy with it.

I'll go with 2 stars. ONLY because we were greeted and shown around once we came in. Dave showed us the price of a dining room table.... we were not there for that, but aside from that he told my husband and I that we would be getting 20% on anything because it was their sale due to presidents day. He didn't ask what our price range was just what kind of couches we were looking for. He OBVIOUSLY started showing us super expensive ones & said "This one here is my best seller you guys." Like ok we know you're lying, but that's what some annoying sales people do. He then showed us a FLOOR MODEL that was $1799, but no delivery would be included. After showing us a few more, I had to ask him to give us time alone to talk about what we wanted to do, he was like 3 feet away from us it was annoying. He said "Yeah sure no problem." He did just that, but as we were walking back to the floor display I see him from the corner of my eye following us and then says "That's a really great deal you guys! Our best seller, but it's discontinued." I had to hold it together because I was already annoyed. To finish this story, we decided why not go with the floor model we're going to get 20% off anyways, and I can see if he's willing to add the 10% off coupon I got online. When we asked he said "Oh we can't give you 20% off. The price is already knocked down." I've worked in retail for 5 years... people know that when someone is misinformed a courtesy is done due to wrong information given. He said no, so as we're walking away we see what looked like a manager ask him what was going on, Dave is pointing at us shaking his head. We left without getting anything, which is ok we went to Nebraska Furniture and we had a respectful and honest gentleman by the name of Carlos who helped us out respecting our decision.
